ArchiveContext  
ArchiveKey  
ArchiveManager Cache of recently decoded archives: - Keep up to N ArchiveHandler's in RAM (this can be large; we don't keep the files open due to the limitations of the java.util.zip API) - Keep up to Y bytes (after padding and overheads) of decoded data on disk (the OS is quite capable of determining what to keep in actual RAM) Always take the lock on ArchiveStoreContext before the lock on ArchiveManager, NOT the other way around.
